<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1188,1467]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1188,1213]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
From Mexico, southward to Guianas, 
<collectingCountry box="[762,833,1188,1212]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[848,902,1189,1212]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[918,1003,1188,1212]" name="Bolivia" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1176,1291,1188,1212]" name="Argentina" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1409,1188,1212]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it shows a disjunct distribution and has been recorded almost all 
<collectingCountry box="[859,930,1224,1248]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[1129,1223,1224,1248]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1235,1303,1224,1248]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Ceará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1316,1432,1224,1248]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,238,1260,1284]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[248,308,1260,1284]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Piauí</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[319,556,1260,1284]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Norte" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Rio Grande do Norte</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[567,666,1260,1284]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Roraima</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[678,790,1260,1284]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[800,888,1260,1284]" country="Brazil" name="Sergipe" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Sergipe</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[945,1053,1260,1284]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues, F. H. G. &amp; Silveira, L. &amp; Jacomo, A. T. A. &amp; Carmignotto, A. P. &amp; Bezerra, A. M. R. &amp; Coelho, D. &amp; Garbogini, H. &amp; Pagnozzi, J. &amp; Hass, A." box="[1070,1313,1260,1284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="589 - 600" refId="ref11317" refString="Rodrigues, F. H. G., Silveira, L., Jacomo, A. T. A., Carmignotto, A. P., Bezerra, A. M. R., Coelho, D., Garbogini, H., Pagnozzi, J. &amp; Hass, A. (2002) Composicao e caracterizacao da fauna de mamiferos do Parque Nacional das Emas, Goias. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 19, 589 - 600." type="journal article" year="2002">
Rodrigues 
<emphasis box="[1191,1240,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Reis, N. R. &amp; Peracchi, A. L. &amp; Pedro, W. A. &amp; Lima, I. P." pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref11214" refString="Reis, N. R., Peracchi, A. L., Pedro, W. A. &amp; Lima, I. P. (2007) Morcegos do Brasil. UEL, Londrina, 253 p." type="book" year="2007">
Reis 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1188,1467]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1332,1357]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Inhabits tropical rainforest, deciduous forests, and cloud forests, roosting at places such as caves, mines, abandoned buildings, and hollow trees (
<bibRefCitation author="Medellin, R. A." box="[689,859,1368,1392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref10653" refString="Medellin, R. A. (1989) Chrotopterus auritus. Mammalian Species, 343, 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1989">Medellín 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Reis, N. R. &amp; Peracchi, A. L. &amp; Pedro, W. A. &amp; Lima, I. P." box="[873,1058,1368,1392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref11214" refString="Reis, N. R., Peracchi, A. L., Pedro, W. A. &amp; Lima, I. P. (2007) Morcegos do Brasil. UEL, Londrina, 253 p." type="book" year="2007">
Reis 
<emphasis box="[931,982,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). We captured 
<specimenCount box="[1229,1383,1368,1392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
in a pasture field near to limestone outcrops (
<geoCoordinate box="[609,782,1404,1431]" degrees="14" direction="south" minutes="30" orientation="latitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" precision="1" seconds="25.4" value="-14.507055">
14 
<superScript attach="left" box="[637,645,1404,1418]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">o</superScript>
30’ 25.4” S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[795,978,1404,1431]" degrees="46" direction="west" minutes="43" orientation="longitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" precision="1" seconds="51.5" value="-46.730972">
46 
<superScript attach="left" box="[822,830,1404,1418]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">o</superScript>
43’ 51.5” W
</geoCoordinate>
) in Alvorada do Norte, GO.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1188,1467]" box="[199,797,1442,1467]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,1442,1467]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Voucher specimen.</emphasis>
